.\" Man page for btrfs-backup-ng status
.TH BTRFS-BACKUP-NG-STATUS 1 "January 2026" "btrfs-backup-ng" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
btrfs-backup-ng-status \- show job status and statistics
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B btrfs-backup-ng status
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Display last run times, snapshot counts, transfer statistics, and overall
health status for configured backup jobs.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-transactions
Show recent transaction history from the transaction log.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-limit " " \fIN\fR
Number of transactions to show. Default: 10.
.SH OUTPUT
The status command shows:
.IP \(bu 2
Last successful run time
.IP \(bu 2
Snapshot counts per volume
.IP \(bu 2
Backup counts per target
.IP \(bu 2
Any errors or warnings
.PP
With \fB\-\-transactions\fR, also shows:
.IP \(bu 2
Recent backup/transfer operations
.IP \(bu 2
Success/failure status
.IP \(bu 2
Transfer sizes and durations
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Show current status:
.B btrfs-backup-ng status
.TP
Show last 20 transactions:
.B btrfs-backup-ng status --transactions --limit 20
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/btrfs-backup-ng/transactions.jsonl
User transaction log.
.TP
.I /var/lib/btrfs-backup-ng/transactions.jsonl
System transaction log.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR btrfs-backup-ng (1),
.BR btrfs-backup-ng-list (1)
